"title": "9155: millennium",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "9155: millennium",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The period of 1,000 years referred to in Revelation chapter 20, during which Satan is bound and believers reign with Jesus Christ. This millennium is understood in different ways: as a period of unparalleled peace and prosperity for the church and the gospel at the end of this age, after which Christ will return (postmillennialism); as the time following Christ's return when he will reign on earth (premillennialism); as a symbolic reference to the period between Christ's first and second comings (amillennialism).</p>\n<h2>Characteristics of the millennium</h2>\n<h3>Satan is bound</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:1-Rev20:3\">REV 20:1–20:3</a></strong> <em>“the Abyss” is the subterranean place of confinement for Satan and evil spirits.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:31\">LUK 8:31</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:29\">MAT 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:7\">MRK 5:7</a></p>\n<h3>Martyred believers are raised to reign with Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:4-Rev20:6\">REV 20:4–20:6</a></strong> <em>Those who have suffered for the gospel receive their promised reward.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:17\">ROM 8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:11-2Tim2:12\">2TI 2:11–2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>Satan's release and final overthrow</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:7-Rev20:10\">REV 20:7–20:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:1-Ezek38:4\">EZK 38:1–38:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:15-Ezek38:16\">EZK 38:15–38:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:18-Ezek38:22\">EZK 38:18–38:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:2-Ezek39:5\">EZK 39:2–39:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:2\">ZEC 14:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:20\">ROM 16:20</a></p>\n<h2>The millennium will be a golden age on earth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:2-Isa2:4\">ISA 2:2–2:4</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:1-Mic4:3\">MIC 4:1–4:3</a> <em>The OT looks forward to a period of universal peace and prosperity on earth. Both pre- and postmillennialists see this as a reference to Jesus Christ's future earthly reign.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:6-Isa11:9\">ISA 11:6–11:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:4-Isa51:5\">ISA 51:4–51:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:25\">ISA 65:25</a></p>\n<h2>The premillennial interpretation</h2>\n<h3>The premillennial order of events</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:11-Rev19:13\">REV 19:11–19:13</a> <em>Jesus Christ's return. Premillennialists understand the events of Revelation chapter 19 to precede those of Revelation chapter 20</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:2-Rev20:3\">REV 20:2–20:3</a> <em>Satan bound for 1,000 years</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:4-Rev20:6\">REV 20:4–20:6</a> <em>a “first resurrection” of believers to share Jesus Christ's reign over the earth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:7-Rev20:10\">REV 20:7–20:10</a> <em>Satan's release and final overthrow</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:11-Rev20:15\">REV 20:11–20:15</a> <em>the general resurrection of all people to face God's judgment</em></p>\n<h3>A first resurrection of believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:22-1Cor15:25\">1CO 15:22–15:25</a></strong> <em>This passage allows the idea of a gap between the resurrection of believers and the eternal age.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16-1Thess4:17\">1TH 4:16–4:17</a></p>\n<h3>God's future earthly reign</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:9\">ZEC 14:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:44\">DAN 2:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:11\">ZEP 3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:16-Zech14:21\">ZEC 14:16–14:21</a></p>\n<h3>Believers will reign with Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:28\">MAT 19:28</a></strong> <em>Premillennialists take this to refer to an earthly reign.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:29-Luke22:30\">LUK 22:29–22:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:2\">1CO 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9-Rev5:10\">REV 5:9–5:10</a></p>\n<h3>Difficulties with premillennialism</h3>\n<p>Scriptures that depict a single resurrection of both the righteous and the wicked:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:2\">DAN 12:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:28-John5:29\">JHN 5:28–5:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:40-Matt13:43\">MAT 13:40–13:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:49-Matt13:50\">MAT 13:49–13:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31-Matt25:32\">MAT 25:31–25:32</a></p>\n<h2>The postmillennial interpretation</h2>\n<h3>The rapid spread of the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:14\">MAT 24:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:10\">MRK 13:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:31-Matt13:33\">MAT 13:31–13:33</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:31-Mark4:32\">MRK 4:31–4:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:18-Luke13:21\">LUK 13:18–13:21</a></p>\n<h3>A future turning to God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:27-Ps22:28\">PSA 22:27–22:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:19-Isa19:24\">ISA 19:19–19:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:11\">ZEC 2:11</a></p>\n<h3>Difficulties with postmillennialism</h3>\n<p>The fortunes of the gospel and the church appear to be at a low ebb before Jesus Christ returns:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:9-Matt24:12\">MAT 24:9–24:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:12-Luke21:17\">LUK 21:12–21:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:1-2Tim3:5\">2TI 3:1–3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:12-2Tim3:13\">2TI 3:12–3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18\">MAT 28:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:33-Acts2:36\">ACT 2:33–2:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:55-Acts7:56\">ACT 7:55–7:56</a></p>\n<h2>The amillennial interpretation</h2>\n<h3>Satan was defeated at Jesus Christ's first coming</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:31\">JHN 12:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:29\">MAT 12:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:27\">MRK 3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:21-Luke11:22\">LUK 11:21–11:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:18-Luke10:20\">LUK 10:18–10:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:14-Col2:15\">COL 2:14–2:15</a></p>\n<h3>Interpreting the ``first resurrection''</h3>\n<p>As a reference to the soul entering heaven after death:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:43\">LUK 23:43</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:7-2Tim4:8\">2TI 4:7–4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:5\">ROM 6:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:6\">EPH 2:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1\">COL 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>Dangers of the amillennialist view</h3>\n<p>The future hope of believers is not only a spiritual reality:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:19-Rom8:21\">ROM 8:19–8:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:1\">REV 21:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:8\">1PE 5:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:19\">1JN 5:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:17\">REV 12:17</a></p>",
